channel.title: Problem with auto cache downloading :'(
channel.description:
So basically my server didnt have a cachedownloader and i added a cachedownload class through a tutorial found on moparscape but when i delete my old cache and hope for it to download my new cache it doesnt and i get a error
[code]RS2 user client - release #317 java.io.FileNotFoundException: C:\xxxxx\main_file_cache.dat (The system cannot find the path specified) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.open(Native Method) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at sign.signlink.run(signlink.java:55) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source) java.io.FileNotFoundException: C:\xxxxxxxxx\main_file_cache.dat (The system cannot find the path specified) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.open(Native Method) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at java.io.RandomAccessFile.<init>(Unknown Source) at sign.signlink.run(signlink.java:55) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source) [/code]
I put xxxxx to block out my servers name
